properties.headline: Marine Weather Statement issued February 16 at 12:14PM CST by NWS Corpus Christi TX
properties.description:
Moist onshore flow over the relatively cooler shelf waters will
lead to patchy sea fog through this afternoon. Visibilities will
generally range from 2 to 5 nautical miles, with patchy dense fog
of 1 nautical mile or less at times in bays and nearshore waters.

Mariners over the Bay Waters and over the Nearshore Coastal
Waters within 20 nautical miles offshore are urged to prepare for
rapidly changing visibilities.

NWSheadline: PATCHY SEA FOG EXPECTED THROUGH THE AFTERNOON
